# Cloudflare Pages serves these response headers (https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/).
# Security hardening for a public launch — purely additive, no app behavior or visual change.
#   - frame-ancestors 'none' + X-Frame-Options: DENY  → the OAuth consent "Allow"
#     button (/oauth/consent) cannot be iframed/clickjacked.
#   - connect-src allowlist  → an XSS/compromised dep cannot exfiltrate the Supabase
#     JWT to an arbitrary host; traffic is pinned to Supabase + the hilka-mcp Worker
#     + Mixpanel's ingestion API (product analytics). The Mixpanel SDK is bundled
#     from npm (not a CDN) and posts events over XHR, so only connect-src widens —
#     script-src and img-src are untouched. Host: api-js.mixpanel.com (US default;
#     api.mixpanel.com / api-eu.mixpanel.com kept for the EU residency option).
#   - 'unsafe-inline' stays on style-src/script-src: the SPA ships an inline module
#     bootstrap and React/Supabase set inline styles; nonces would break it. The CSP
#     still blocks object/base/frame + arbitrary connect/exfil, which is the win.
# If a future endpoint (e.g. Supabase Realtime over a new host) is blocked, widen
# connect-src minimally rather than dropping the policy.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; connect-src 'self' https://htrvknxzunkqxcqsqxpm.supabase.co wss://htrvknxzunkqxcqsqxpm.supabase.co https://hilka-mcp.sviatik2408.workers.dev https://api-js.mixpanel.com https://api.mixpanel.com https://api-eu.mixpanel.com; form-action 'self'; frame-src 'none'
